title: Undefeated Atlanta hammers Houston
text:
Photo: Brett Coomer /Houston Chronicle Image 1 of / 1 1 It wasn’t the outcome Arian Foster was looking for as the running back returned to play in his first game from a groin injury. Foster carried eight times for 10 yards in Houston’s loss to Atlanta.
Photo: Brett Coomer /Houston Chronicle It wasn’t the outcome Arian Foster was looking for as the running... Undefeated Atlanta hammers Houston 1 / 1 Back to Gallery ATLANTA — Devonta Freeman just wanted a chance.
Wow, he’s sure taking advantage of it.
Dazzling as both a runner and a receiver, Freeman had another three-touchdown game for the Atlanta Falcons, who remained unbeaten with a 48-21 rout of the hapless Houston Texans on Sunday.
Nothing went right for the Texans (1-3). Quarterback Ryan Mallett had an awful day and was replaced by Brian Hoyer after the Falcons built a 42-0 lead.
For more, visit ExpressNews.com
